content:
Hi @everyone !👋  Thrilled to introduce **ArchiDrawGPT**—an AI agent built to support enterprise architects and anyone stepping into architecture modeling.

Architecture models are essential for large enterprises—they align strategy, processes, and technology. But creating them, especially following TOGAF and ArchiMate standards, can be complex and time-consuming.

I built *ArchiDrawGPT* from a deep desire to bring GenAI into serious architectural work—giving a helping hand to junior and medior architects, and making it easier for anyone to create solid architecture models. This frees up expert architects to focus on solving critical business challenges instead of getting stuck in diagrams.

Ever paused and asked yourself, is this a business service or an application service? Or should this be modeled as a capability or a process? These aren’t just technical questions—they shape how organizations see and solve problems. ArchiDrawGPT helps navigate these choices and makes modeling more accessible. Attached is an example architecture diagram generated by *ArchiDrawGPT* for credit lending.

Building this tool showed me AI’s potential to make enterprise architecture smarter and more inclusive.

Try it out here: [https://chatgpt.com/g/g-6803803bd90c8191aa5d78df4484e739-archidrawgpt]
I’d love your feedback and ideas! Building ArchiDrawGPT also taught me a lot about AI’s limits & the messy challenges. There’s more to explore, and I’d love your feedback, thoughts, or ideas.

content:
Dear contributors dear <@1352785241252565174>. In my onboarding today I discussed with Oscar on which KPIs we will manage the community and to ensure progress in creating something valuable. I just want to share my thoughts and I am happy to learn what you think about this. Draft: 

To help us steer this amazing GenAI community as it grows, I’d like to suggest a lightweight but powerful KPI system. It’s designed to balance long-term vision with day-to-day insights:

Top-Level KPIs (big picture)

Member Growth & Reach – Are we growing globally + inclusively?

Engagement Rate – How many members actively participate?

Innovation Output – Are we co-creating GenAI knowledge and projects?

Influence Score – Are we making waves outside the community?

Mid-Level KPIs (community health)

Activation Rate – Do new members engage in their first week?

Contributor % – Are we enabling broad participation?

Response Time – Are questions + ideas being picked up fast?

Retention – Are members staying and returning?

Ops-Level KPIs (daily signals)

Post-to-Comment Ratio – Are we sparking real dialogue?

Event Attendance vs. Sign-ups – Are sessions landing well?

Moderation Flags – Is the space safe and respectful?

Cross-Channel Activity – Are members engaging across Discord, GitHub, etc.?

This system gives us clarity and flexibility—and helps us keep this space meaningful, global, and aligned with the GenAI mission.

Happy to co-create this further—open to feedback, iterations, or starting a mini-pilot together if it this will help.

👉 Join a collaborative session to co‑shape open‑source AI guardrails—and earn recognition across the Gen AI Global community.

🌐 Towards a Global Charter for Ethical AI – A Gen AI Global Initiative 🤝

It is widely accepted that open‑source models hold the key to inclusive AI. During our ethics discussions, a proposal surfaced: could a UN‑style charter for AI—developed under the Gen AI Global banner—fill today’s governance gap? Could this be the foundation for global alignment in open‑source AI? 🤔

content:
Hi everyone! I’d love to join and co-curate the AI Ethics channel. My vision is to create a space for thoughtful, inclusive inquiry, where we explore how AI can reflect—and reshape—our world.

Core questions we might explore together (my suggestion today at the orientatin call with <@1352785241252565174> :

- How does AI mirror, magnify, or mask human bias?
- Who is included—and who is excluded—by today’s AI systems?
- What ethical frameworks can guide us toward greater access, transparency, and justice?
- How do we ensure marginalized voices help shape the future of AI?

I come to this not as an expert, but as a passionate learner and advocate for digital inclusion: making sure that everyone has the power, tools, and voice to participate in the AI era.

If selected, I’d like to launch our first discussion under the theme:
“Bias is a Mirror: What AI Reflects Back at Us”

Let’s spark bold conversations and build ethical awareness—together.
